$interpreted: Sherlock: Not bad, not bad. Such exquisite handiwork. Only I, Sherlock, could truly reconstruct this!
Sherlock: Finished with the repair...but even if I activate your core, your memory is heavily encrypted. I won't be able to unlock it.
Sherlock: Until I figure out who produced you, I won't be at ease...
Sherlock: Let's turn you on and see how you look.
Maria: Core reactivated, confirming user. Please state the user's name, or create a new user.
Sherlock: Sher...Ned Garcia Alznar.
Maria: Detecting model type identical to the target, Sherlock──
Sherlock: !!!
Sherlock: Whooo! Scared me there! Luckily I forced a shutdown just in time...
Sherlock: Never thought you were sent by the Mechanical Territory to capture me...I wonder if any more robots are coming?
Sherlock: No, I can't let that rascal take you away!
Sherlock: Good thing I turned you on to check things out. Your existence is much too dangerous.
Sherlock: All I want is to have a nice life with Lisa. Can't blame me.
Clark: Maria!
Clark: What are you doing!
Sherlock: I must destroy her! Don't try to stop me!
Lisa: Father! Are you okay!?
Ned: Clark, what is going on with you two?
Clark: I came back to take Maria and I saw Sherlock holding a weapon, about to attack her!
Ned: Father! Why would you──
Sherlock: It has nothing to do with you!
Lisa: Father!
Sherlock: Since you won't let me destroy her, take her and get the hell out of here!
Clark: You...
Sherlock: You deaf? Scram!
Ned: Clark, wait!
Ned: I'm sorry, Clark.
Ned: Lisa just asked Father what happened. He wouldn't say why he wanted to attack Maria.
Clark: Ah! That's right––
Ned: Clark?
Clark: (That time Maria crashed, she mentioned Sherlock...)
Clark: (Then, when I asked Maria, she didn't remember anything. I didn't think anything of it...could there be some connection here?)
Ned: Clark, did you remember something important?
Clark: No, I have no clue. Perhaps Sherlock found something when he was repairing Maria.
Ned: Hmm...
Ned: Oh yeah, Father said he already fixed Maria. Said you don't have to carry her.
Ned: In order to express our apologies, Lisa and I prepared some food for you. Please, take it.
Clark: ...Thank you.
Ned: I'm going to head back. You take care. Safe travels!
Clark: ...Should've had Sherlock change the position of this 'on' button.
Maria: Core reactivated, confirming user. Please state the user's name, or create a new user.
Clark: ...Clark Shot
Maria: Master, Maria at your service. Please, issue a command.
Clark: Maria, why are you acting so weird...
Maria: Unable to discern your command.
Clark: Maria? You...do you recognize me?
Maria: Esteemed master, please issue a command.
Clark: Maria, you didn't call me that before...
Clark: She just said "core reactivated"...
Clark: So it's just like last time? Your memory was wiped clean?
Clark: Or, did Sherlock do something to you when he repaired you...
Clark: (Wait a second, something looks off...)
Clark: (When I first found Maria, there were some parts that I couldn't figure out.)
Clark: (Did Sherlock put them back on Maria?)
Maria: Esteemed master, Maria is unable to decipher your command.
Clark: (So that means this is what Maria originally looked like...)
Clark: Maria, do you remember who produced you?
Maria: Maria was produced by...
Maria: By...by...
Clark: Maria!? Are you okay?
Maria: ...The core has been partially damaged, the core has been partially damaged. It will not affect this unit's functions. Waiting for auto-repair is suggested.
Clark: Well, can you tell me why you left the Mechanical Territory?
Maria: To execute an urgent mission, esteemed Master.
Clark: Mission? What mission?
Maria: It...it is...

Maria: It is...the core has been partially damaged, the core has been partially damaged. It will not affect this unit's functions. 
Waiting for auto-repair is suggested.
Clark: Auto-repair?
Clark: I'm not sure right now. So you mean we can wait until later?
Clark: Hmm...
Clark: Ah, that's it!
Clark: Sorry Chu Chu, almost forgot about you.
Chu Chu: Chu!!
Clark: Chu Chu!!
Clark: Maria, why...!
Maria: It wanted to attack Master.
Clark: Chu Chu did not want to attack me!
Maria: Maria must protect the safety of Master.
Clark: Maria, you don't remember Chu Chu? You are its master. You used to like Chu Chu so much...
Maria: Maria is executing a search.
Maria: The described memory could not be found, esteemed master.
Clark: It's my fault...I shouldn't have left you alone with Sherlock.
Maria: Esteemed master, please issue a command.
Clark: Tomorrow...we've got to hit the road for the Desert Kingdom. We'll rest early today.
Maria: As you wish, Master.
Clark: ...So, you don't remember when we got chased and beaten for doing a dine and dash?
Maria: I do not remember, esteemed master.
Clark: Or when you fought with Sophie and Rune the first time we met them?
Maria: I do not remember, esteemed master.
Clark: Why are you so far away from me?
Maria: Based on my calculations, this is the optimal distance for defending against attacks from all sides. It is for Master's safety.
Clark: We made it back just in time...
Clark: Maria, you wait here. I'll go get the tickets and find a sailor to confirm everything.
Maria: As you wish, Master.
Clark: Well, you can tell the orders came directly from the Queen. The sailors are acting all polite and friendly...
Maria: Chu Chu...Chu Chu...
Clark: Maria! What were you just saying?
Maria: Maria was not saying anything.
Maria: Esteemed master, please issue a command.
Clark: ...Maria.
Clark: (Was she mimicking the sound of a gull...or is some of her memory still intact?)
Clark: (Will I be able to find something that will help Maria in the Mechanical Territory...? I mean, I'm not her true master.)
Sailor: Guests of the Queen, you may board the ship!
Clark: Coming right away, please wait just a moment!
Clark: (...Is this really for the best? I...)
Maria: Esteemed master?
Clark: ...Maria, I wish you would remember me.
Clark: So we're going to the Mechanical Territory to find some way that will bring back your memory.
Maria: As you wish, Master.
Clark: But if you turn back into the Maria that I know, that may stop you from carrying out your original mission.
Clark: I said it before; your setting allows you to make your own decision.
Clark: So, you need to decide things for yourself, okay? Do you want to come with me, or stay here?
Clark: Maria? Are your memories coming back—
Maria: Maria's settings are such that she must obey her user's commands.
Maria: Esteemed master, please issue a command.
